#PyBayenv must be run on a Linux computer.
#The input format is the GENEPOP format.
#Please examine the bundled files for the exact input formats.

#Run
source pybayenv.conf

#For option menu type
pybayenv -h

#Example: Run eight parallel runs of BAYENV on 131 SNPs from African Maize (Westengen et al. 2014).
pybayenv -f all_snps-staha.gp -e environ_var-staha.env -n 3 -z 1 -p 8 -i 10000 -E 0.2

#The BAYENV2 program is available at https://gcbias.org/bayenv/ and the binary must be copied to the /bin directory.
#Please remember to cite Coop et al. 2010 (BAYENV) and GÃ¼nther, Torsten and Graham Coop 2013 (BAYENV 2.0) when PyBayenv is used.

#NB In case of problems with PyBayenv, please make sure that the binary of BAYENV2 may run on the computer (e.g. ./bin/bayenv2)

